{
  "texts": [
    "PromptingStrategies Specialized for Recommender Systems.",
    "The planning ability emerging from LLMs is the key to distinguishing them from other language models [184].",
    "In general tasks with LLMs, researchers use methods such as Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting to stimulate the logical reasoning ability of LLMs for solving complex problems [23,85].",
    "As for LLM-RS, leveraging LLMs for recommender systems can also employ prompting strategies to further improve the performance of recommendations [83,167].",
    "In addition, due to the user and item settings of the recommendation task, the prompting strategy needs to be customized based on the specific user needs in recommender systems."
  ]
}